# Beaver Architecture Invariants

## Contracts

- Pub/Sub message schemas live in `packages/shared/contracts/*.json` (source of truth).
- TypeScript: `packages/shared/src/messages.ts` (zod). Python: `packages/shared-py/`.
- All messages carry `schema_version`, `trace_id`, `published_at`.
- Use constants from `@beaver/shared` / `beaver_shared.constants` — never hardcode topic/bucket names.

## Idempotency

- Documents: `content_hash` (sha256) + `document_id = doc-{county}-{hash16}`.
- Jobs: `job_id = job-{county_id}-{date}`.
- Projects: MERGE upsert on `project_id` / `tracking_number` — never duplicate rows.

## Project Lifecycle

Stages: `subcommittee` → `approved` → `bidding` → `awarded` → `closed`.
Projects accumulate data across meetings via MERGE, not INSERT.

## Do Not Build

- Discovery Engine integration (unresolved).
- Full F5 per-user LLM matching (scaffold only — see personalization.ts TODOs).
- Frontend or Notifier beyond stubs.

## Language Split

- Node: dispatcher, classifier, personalization.
- Python: scraper, analyzer (required libraries are Python-only).

## Error Handling

- Structural scraper failures → circuit breaker on Firestore county (`broken_until` cooldown).
- Transient failures → Pub/Sub retry → DLQ after 5 attempts.
- Propagate `trace_id` through every message for observability.
